  "suggestion": "Survival != fitness: organisms live long but starve. Resource scarcity, not predation, is the limiter.; Efficiency (0.398) is the critical bottleneck—lowest component and dragging goal score. Organisms reach max age (500) but end critically low on energy (organism 2: 2 energy, organisms 0/3: dead). This suggests resourceAttraction and harvestThreshold mismatch: organisms are underfed despite long lifespans. Two dead organisms confirm energy depletion risk. Root cause: organisms move/consume energy but fail to gather enough resources. Fix: (1) boost resourceAttraction 0.3→0.7 to find scattered resources more effectively, (2) lower harvestThreshold 0.6→0.35 to trigger feeding earlier and more frequently, (3) increase energyConserve 0.4→0.75 to reduce per-cycle burn rate. Jellyfish and crawler archetypes both need this adjustment. Secondary gain: better energy stability should improve survivalRate.",
